\pard\nowidctlpar\cf2\b\fs28\par
\cf0\fs24 General\cf2\fs28\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\qj\cf0\b0\fs20 Worms Armageddon now runs under the majority of Windows 2000 / XP / Vista / 7 Platforms. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 1, improved in 3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 It is now possible to successfully minimise W:A in all areas, within the front end and in-game. To minimise the game in the front end, position the mouse cursor at the bottom of the screen and click; to minimise from in-game, select the appropriate option from the Escape menu. \b Shift\b0 +\b Escape\b0  also works as a minimisation hotkey both in the front end and in-game. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 1, improved in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The language used for front end and in-game text can now be chosen manually from the Options menu. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.26.4)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The game has been fully translated to \b Russian\b0 , and support for Cyrillic has been added for chat, WormNET game names, worm and team names. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Translatable strings have been moved into external text files, located under the DATA\\User\\Languages directory. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.7.0.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}It is possible to take screen-shots, both in the front end and in-game. To do so, press the \b Pause\b0  key. Screenshots are saved in PNG format, are named \b screen\i NNNN\i0 .png\b0  and are stored in \b User\\Capture\b0  under your main W:A folder. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.17, improved in v3.6.24.1, v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}W:A now uses 32-bit colour graphics modes both in the front end and in-game. Internally it still uses 8-bit palettised graphics, with a software renderer converting to 32-bit colour in real time. DirectDraw and Direct3D rendering backends are available. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.31.2b, improved in v3.7.0.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The colour scheme used for allies (red, blue, green, yellow, magenta, cyan) can now be modified to allow those with certain types of colour deficiency to be able to easily distinguish problematic colour pairs. (It is targeted particularly towards protanomaly.) This switch has been added to the Options menu, replacing the terrain editing button in that screen. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.22.1)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}In case of an unrecoverable error, W:A will save an error report to the file \b errorlog.txt\b0 , and a minidump to \b crash.dmp\b0 . \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}An option has been added to load WormKit modules (DLL files beginning with "wk") on startup. Previously this was achieved by using a loader program (WormKit.exe) or a modified DLL (WormKitDS). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.7.0.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Certain settings may be configured with the help of included registry scripts, which can be found in the \b Tweaks\b0  subdirectory. Before v3.6.30.0 introduced a graphical user interface to configure these options, using the registry scripts and direct registry editing was the only way to set these options. (See \b Footnote 4\b0 .)\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Updates for CD editions of the game are distributed as a self-contained installer, which can automatically download and install prerequisites and detect common mistakes. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\cf3\b\fs28\par
\cf0\fs24 Front End\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\b0\fs20 If you have achieved a Gold Medal in a mission, you can now adjust the number of Attempts by left- or right-clicking the number. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}It is possible to precisely adjust certain game settings by holding \b Shift\b0  and left- or right-clicking the settings to increase or decrease the values by 1. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The Scheme combo box now allows you to navigate to subfolders under the \b User\\Schemes\b0  folder. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}A new utility option editor has been added, allowing to edit the crate probabilities, delays etc. of utilities. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}It is possible to play TCP/IP online games directly, bypassing WormNET. To host, click the \b Direct TCP/IP\b0  button on the network selection screen; to join, enter the host's IP address in the field near the \b Direct TCP/IP\b0  button, and click the button or press \b Enter\b0 . A port may be specified using the \i IPAddress\b\i0 :\b0\i Port\i0  format. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7, improved in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}It is now possible to set the TCP port used for hosting games. This setting is in the Network Configuration screen, and affects both WormNET and Direct IP games. Games hosted on a port other than the default one, \b 17011\b0 , will be inaccessible to game versions prior to 3.6.28.0. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}W:A will now attempt to automatically forward the port used for hosting using \b UPnP\b0  when hosting WormNET and Direct IP games. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}W:A now auto-detects the user's IP address using a reply from the WormNET server. This should make manually configuring the external IP address unnecessary in most cases. The IP address can still be overridden using the "Force IP address" checkbox. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The default Server List file will now automatically log you onto WormNET using the nickname entered in the main Network Menu (this works because logins are currently not enabled). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.23.0, improved in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}WormNET flags have been added for the following countries: \cf4 Chile\cf0 , \cf4 Serbia\cf0 , \cf4 Slovenia\cf0 , \cf4 Lebanon\cf0 , \cf4 Moldova\cf0 , \cf4 Ukraine\cf0 , \cf4 Latvia\cf0 , \cf4 Slovakia\cf0 , \cf4 Costa Rica\cf0 , \cf4 Estonia\cf0 , \cf4 China\cf0 , \cf4 Colombia\cf0 , \cf4 Ecuador\cf0 , \cf4 Uruguay\cf0 , \cf4 Venezuela\cf0 , \cf4 Algeria\cf0 , \cf4 Belarus\cf0 , \cf4 Bulgaria\cf0 , \cf4 Egypt\cf0 , \cf4 El Salvador\cf0 , \cf4 Guatemala\cf0 , \cf4 Jamaica\cf0 , \cf4 Kazakhstan\cf0 , \cf4 South Korea\cf0 , \cf4 Lithuania\cf0 , \cf4 Macedonia\cf0 , \cf4 Marshall Islands\cf0 , \cf4 Peru\cf0 , \cf4 Saudi Arabia\cf0 , \cf4 Taiwan\cf0  and \cf4 United Arab Emirates\cf0 . \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.23.0, v3.6.24.2, v3.6.28.0, v3.6.29.0, v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}An "Ignore" feature was added in WormNET. To ignore/unignore someone, hold \b Ctrl\b0  and double-click on their nickname in the nickname list, or type \b /ignore\b0  or \b /unignore\b0  followed by their nickname. Ignored nicknames are shown in red in the nickname list. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 2)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Web and E-mail URLs are now automatically parsed and converted to hyperlinks in message histories (WormNET, LAN and host/join screen). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}A host can now limit the number of players joining, by resizing the player list box. To do so, click and drag the thick bottom edge of this box. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7, improved in v3.6.25.1a)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}In front end network screens, entering the command "\b /u\b0 " or "\b /url\b0 " will now copy a \b wa://address-of-host\b0  URL into the clipboard, which can be used by other players to join the game directly (even for a WormNET game). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0, improved in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}An \b Advanced Options\b0  screen has been added, which allows configuring settings previously only configurable using registry scripts and direct registry editing. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\b\fs24\par
Maps and the Map editor\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\b0\fs20 While clicking rapidly through map thumbnails, you may accidentally skip past a good looking one. Now you can backtrack with a Shift+Click. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Imported colour maps are saved in PNG format (with metadata) and usable in online games. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Colour PNG maps may be loaded directly in the map editor, with the following limitations:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540 Maps may have up to \cf4 64\cf0  colours (65 including black) if graphical glitches are to be avoided; \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Maps may have up to \cf4 96\cf0  colours (97 including black), but then soil textures (the background that appears when land is blown up) and the background graphics (clouds, etc.) will be disabled, and the destroyed-soil border will be solid grey; \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7, improved in v3.6.25.1a)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Maps may have up to \cf4 112\cf0  colours (113 including black), but then (additionally to the limitations above) the background gradient will be re-rendered using the map colours and whatever free space there will be left in the colour palette. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.25.1a, improved in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Maps can be organised into folders underneath User\\SavedLevels, which can then be navigated in the map editor combo box. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}PNG maps may have dimensions other than 1920\'d7696. A cavern map may now be up to 32504 pixels wide or 32600 pixels tall; an island is limited to being 28408 wide or 30552 tall. The minimum map size is 640\'d732. A map's width and height must be divisible by 8. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 To draw lines: click a point with the brush, hold down Shift and click an end point. This can be used to draw many connecting lines if Shift is held down the whole time. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 1)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}To cycle through available brush sizes, rotate the mouse wheel; to draw vertical/horizontal lines, hold Ctrl; to move the mouse cursor at \'bc speed, hold Alt. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 1)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}You may now control the number of Placement Holes, the girdered holes that are automatically created when the game detects there is not enough room to randomly place objects. This is done by left- or right-clicking the circled-girder icon, which displays the current number of Holes; holding \b Shift\b0  allows you to fine tune the value, otherwise it skips from 0 to 18 to 32 to 48 and then to the maximum of 300. Holding \b Ctrl\b0  while clicking Reseed will force it to try for as many Holes as it can get. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.25.1a, improved in v3.6.28.0, v3.7.0.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}A slider has been added to the map editor, which allows controlling the range of complexity in randomly generated maps. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.31.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\b\fs24\par
Game\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\b0\fs20 It is now possible to choose any in-game resolution within the capability of the video driver / hardware, with the only limit being a minimum of 640\'d7480. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 1, improved in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\qj It is now possible to play with up to \b 48\b0  Worms if all players are using v3.6.28.0 or later. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}It is now possible to play games with just one team, or with teams of just one allied colour. In such cases, the game will only end in a draw (when all teams surrender or are eliminated). This works for both "multiplayer" and "online" games. When an online game is started without anyone else joining, it will act like an offline game. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Holding the \b Shift\b0  key when walking causes controlled worms to not change the direction in which they are facing. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.20.1)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Utilities can be selected with the key usually located under the Escape key (the key used for typing the \b `\b0  and \b ~\b0  characters on U.S. keyboard layouts). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 1, improved in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}A thought bubble can be displayed above the active worm by pressing \b T\b0 . \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 1, improved in v3.6.19.7)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}It is now possible to enable certain "testing" game options, which are meant to allow playtesting certain game options which may be buggy or significantly change the game's behaviour. See the change log for v3.6.28.0 for more information. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0, improved in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}An AFK (Away From Keyboard) mode was added, activated by entering \b /afk\b0  or \b /away\b0  in the chat, in-game or in the Join lobby. The game will automatically skip your turns while this mode is activated. If enabled during worm placement, the worm will be automatically teleported to a random spot. In the Join lobby, your Ready light bulb will be automatically activated when the host lights up. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7, improved in 3.6.23.0, v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}During a game, players may now use \b Ctrl+PageDown\b0  to initiate "chat pinning", in which the chat panel is displayed even when it is not "in focus". This allows a player to play while reading what the other players are saying. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The network chat panel can now be resized using \b Ctrl+Up\b0  and \b Ctrl+Down\b0 . \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Pressing \b Ctrl\b0 +\b Home\b0  will enable "Home Lock", making the camera remain centred on the current worm. Pressing \b Home\b0  disables it. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Players may now view the weapon panel for their team at any time, including during other players' turns. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}When there are several local teams with different team colours, a menu of team colours is displayed at the bottom of the weapon panel in these cases, allowing the inventory of any local team to be viewed by clicking the team's colour swatch. Similarly, it is possible to view the weapon panel of all ally team colours. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Replays (both instant-replays in offline games, and automatic game recordings): \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7, improved in v3.6.19.17, v3.6.21.1, v3.6.23.0, v3.6.24.1)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540\qj To pause playback, press \b S\b0 .\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}To step one frame while paused, press \b S\b0 .\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The playback speed can be controlled with the top number keys 1 \endash  9. The progression is geometric in pairs: the keys correspond to 1\'d7,1.5\'d7,2\'d7,3\'d7,4\'d7,6\'d7,8\'d7,12\'d7,16\'d7.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Holding 0 allows setting higher coefficients: pressing 1 \endash  9 while holding 0 corresponds to 24\'d7,32\'d7,48\'d7,64\'d7,96\'d7,128\'d7,192\'d7,256\'d7,384\'d7. The speeds are, however, limited to the processing capacity of your machine.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Holding Shift while pressing a speed key or key combination will slow down playback, otherwise it will be speeded up. \par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}To set a "bookmark" at the current position during playback of a game recording, press \b M\b0 . When using "Playback at", the game sets the bookmark at the specified position and fast-forwards the replay until the position is reached.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}To rewind an automatic game recording to the current bookmarked position, or to the beginning of the replay file if no bookmark has been set, press \b R\b0 .\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}To clear the bookmarked position and restart playback from the beginning, press \b Shift\b0 +\b R\b0 .\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 Holding down the left mouse button, or enabling \b Scroll Lock\b0  will prevent the game from automatically moving the camera. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.21.1, improved in v3.6.26.4)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540 Holding \b Shift\b0  while activating \b Scroll Lock\b0  will cause it not to be deactivated at the beginning of your next turn. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Holding \b Control\b0  while activating \b Scroll Lock\b0  will make mouse movement not move the game camera, unless the left mouse button is held down. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 Holding \b Shift\b0  now causes the mouse sensitivity to be multiplied by \b 4\b0 . Holding the middle mouse button does the same. With both combined, the multiplier becomes \b 16\b0 . \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The Mortar and Homing Missile now have shiny new launchers that are coloured differently, to make them easily distinguishable from the Bazooka and Homing Pigeon. The Bazooka also has a makeover. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.22.1)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}In-game sound effects are now played in \b stereo\b0 . \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The hotkey \b Alt+Delete\b0  toggles transparency for labels. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.26.4)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Pressing \b Space\b0  during the playback of a recorded game will now skip to the beginning of the next turn. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\b\fs24\par
Game settings (schemes)\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\b0\fs20 The turn time can now be set to an infinite value. The game will then display a forward turn time counter, starting at zero. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.17, improved in v3.6.25.1a)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The number of in-game hazardous objects (Mines and Oil Drums) is now customisable. The setting can be adjusted in the Scheme Options editor by Shift+clicking the Mine/Oil Drum button. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The Round Time is normally measured in minutes, however it can also be adjusted up to 128 seconds in steps of 1 second. The way this is done is a little strange \emdash  you need to go below 0 minutes, and then left- and right-clicking will have a "backwards" effect on the number of seconds. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}It is now possible to play a match which lasts exactly one round even in the event of a draw. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}"Random worm order" has been added as a third "Worm Select" option. Enabling this mode will cause a team's worms to be selected randomly every time the team gets a turn, instead of cycling through in a fixed order. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}It is now possible to specify the amount of Jet Pack fuel, however currently this can only be done using external scheme editors. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\b\fs24\par
Keyboard\b0\fs20\par
The following keyboard controls are available (in addition to the controls documented in the game manual):\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 Global:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540\b Shift\b0 +\b Escape\b0  - minimise the game. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Pause\b0  - capture a screenshot. Screenshots are saved in PNG format, are named \b screen\i NNNN\i0 .png\b0  and are stored in \b User\\Capture\b0  under your main W:A folder. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.17, improved in v3.6.24.1, v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 Front end:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540\b Escape\b0  - go back to the previous screen, or exit the game when at the main menu. \cf7\fs14 (improved in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 Front end, chat edit controls:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540\b Enter\b0  - send line.\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Up\b0 /\b Down\b0  - select previous/next message from history. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 1)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}PageUp\b0 /\b PageDown\b0  - select previous/next recipient from history. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 1)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 Game:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540\b `\b0  (key used for typing ` and ~ on U.S. keyboard layouts) - select / cycle utilities. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 1, improved in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Shift\b0  + \b Left\b0 /\b Right\b0  - walk without changing facing direction. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.20.1)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}T\b0  - display thought bubble. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.5 Beta 1, improved in v3.6.19.7)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Shift\b0  (hold) - increase mouse sensitivity. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Alt\b0 +\b F4\b0  - immediately return to front end / close replay.\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Shift\b0 +\b Pause\b0  - re-set the palette (when using an 8-bit graphics mode). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Ctrl\b0 +\b Home\b0  - enable "Home Lock" (continuously centre the camera on the current worm). Pressing \b Home\b0  disables it. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Alt\b0 +\b Delete\b0  - toggle transparency for labels. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.26.4)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Scroll Lock\b0  - lock camera. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.21.1, improved in v3.6.26.4)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Shift\b0  + \b Scroll Lock\b0  - lock camera, and do not unlock it at the beginning of the next turn. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Ctrl\b0  + \b Scroll Lock\b0  - lock camera, and ignore mouse movement (unless the left mouse button is held down). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Ctrl \b0 + \b Up\b0 /\b Down\b0  - resize chat panel. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Ctrl \b0 + \b PageDown\b0 /\b PageUp\b0  - pin/unpin chat panel. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 Game chat:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540\b F1\b0\endash\b F6\b0  - send private message (add "\b /msg \b0\i player\i0 " to the chat edit).\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Ctrl\b0  + \b F1\b0\endash\b F6\b0  - ignore/unignore player (same as "\b /ignore \b0\i player\i0 " or "\b /unignore \b0\i player\i0 ").\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}F9\b0\endash\b F11\b0  - send team message (add "\b /\b0\i colour\i0 " to the chat edit).\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 Replay playback:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540\b S\b0  - pause playback / advance one frame. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.17)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540\qj\b 1\b0\endash\b 9\b0  - set playback speed (to 1\'d7,1.5\'d7,2\'d7,3\'d7,4\'d7,6\'d7,8\'d7,12\'d7,16\'d7 respectively). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}0\b0  + \b 1\b0\endash\b 9\b0  - set faster playback speed (24\'d7,32\'d7,48\'d7,64\'d7,96\'d7,128\'d7,192\'d7,256\'d7,384\'d7 respectively). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Shift\b0  + \b 1\b0\endash\b 7\b0  - set slow-motion playback speed (to 1\'d7,\u8532?\'d7,\'bd\'d7,\u8531?\'d7,\'bc\'d7,1/6\'d7,1/8\'d7 respectively). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 Replay playback (recorded games only):\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540\b M\b0  - set bookmark to current position. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}R\b0  - restart playback from beginning, or from bookmark if one is set. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.23.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Shift\b0 +\b R\b0  - clear bookmark and restart playback from the beginning. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.24.1)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Space\b0  - skip until the beginning of the next turn. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\b\fs24\par
Integration and Command-Line Parameters\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\b0\fs20 W:A now automatically creates self-contained recordings of all played games, and saves them to \b User\\Games\b0  under your main W:A folder with a \b .WAgame \b0 extension. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540 Double-click one of them to play back the associated game.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Right-click a replay to display a menu of available actions:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li900\b Playback\b0  - plays the replay as usual;\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Playback at...\b0  - starts playing from a certain point in the replay; \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.24.1)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Extract Map\b0  - extracts the map used in the game and saves it to the \b User\\SavedLevels\b0  folder (with the same file name as the replay); \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.15)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Extract Scheme\b0  - extracts the scheme used in the game and saves it to the \b User\\Schemes\b0  folder (with the same file name as the replay); \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.17)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Export Video...\b0  - renders a series of frames from the replay as images; \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.24.1)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Export Log\b0  - creates a text summary of the replay, containing certain detailed information and statistics; \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.21.2)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Sanitize\b0  - creates a copy of a replay with all private chat messages removed; \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Repair\b0  - repairs certain errors in replay files. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.26.5)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 People hosting Direct IP games may now offer links in the format \b wa://address-of-host\b0 , and launching this link will cause W:A to automatically launch and join the hosted game. \fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\fs20\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The command-line parameters accepted by \b WA.exe\b0  are:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540 Replay parameters (also accessible by right-clicking \b .WAgame\b0  files):\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li900\b /play\b0\~\i Path\\To\\Replay.WAgame\i0\~- plays a replay. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.7)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/playat\b0\~\i Path\\To\\Replay.WAgame\i0\~[\i time\i0 ] - plays a replay starting from a specific moment. If time isn't specified on the command-line, a dialog box is displayed allowing the time to be entered. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.24.1)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/getmap\b0\~\i Path\\To\\Replay.WAgame\i0\~- extract the map from the specified replay to your\~\b User\\SavedLevels\b0\~folder. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.19.15)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/getscheme\b0\~\i Path\\To\\Replay.WAgame\i0\~- extract the scheme from the specified replay to your\~\b User\\Schemes\b0\~folder. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.25.1a)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/getvideo\b0\~\i Path\\To\\Replay.WAgame\i0\~[\i FPS-divider\i0\~[\i start-time\i0\~[\i end-time\i0\~[\i X-resolution\i0\~[\i Y-resolution\i0\~[\i prefix\i0 ]]]]]] - export frames from the specified replay to your\~\b User\\Capture\b0\~folder. If no arguments are specified on the command-line, a dialog box is displayed allowing said options to be entered. If less than 6 arguments are specified, the defaults are to export the entire replay (or until its end), at a resolution of 640\'d7480. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.24.1, improved in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/getlog\b0\~\i Path\\To\\Replay.WAgame\i0\~- export a text log of the replay. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.21.2)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/sanitize\b0\~\i Path\\To\\Replay.WAgame\i0\~- remove private messages from a replay. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.24.1)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/repair\b0\~\i Path\\To\\Replay.WAgame\i0\~- repairs certain errors in replays (currently regarding intrinsic maps). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.26.5)\cf0\fs20\par
\i{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Path\\To\\Replay.WAgame\i0\~- plays the replay (the file must have a .WAgame extension). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540 Network-related parameters:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li900\b /host\b0\~- host a Direct IP game with default options. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}wa:host\b0 [\i parameters\i0 ] - host a Direct IP game with optional parameters (see \b Footnote 3\b0 ). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}wa://\b0 [\i hostname\i0 ][\i parameters\i0 ] - join a Direct IP game with optional parameters. If no host specified, host one instead. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540 Other parameters:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li900\b /nointro\b0\~- disables the intro sequence. Can also be permanently disabled in the Advanced Options screen.\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/q\b0\~or\~\b /quiet\b0\~- suppress some error message dialog boxes. Useful for batch replay operations. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.29.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/register\b0\~- re-register replay and URL associations (used by the W:A update installer). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/wk\b0  and \b /nowk\b0\~- enables and disables loading WormKit modules, respectively. Overrides the registry setting. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.7.0.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/wkargs\b0\~- ignore following command-line parameters. Can be used to pass parameters to WormKit modules. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.7.0.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}/langdir\b0  \i Path\i0  - override language file search path. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.7.0.0)\cf0\fs20\par
