\pard\nowidctlpar\b General\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\qj\b0\fs20 Worms Armageddon now runs under the majority of Windows 2000 and XP Platforms.\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 It is now possible to successfully minimise W:A in all areas, within the front end and in-game.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\par
\b\fs24 Front End\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\b0\fs20 Double mouse clicks are now treated as single clicks where convenient, for example when paging through a list box of schemes or maps.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Game schemes can now include super weapons, as long as the host has \ldblquote Full Wormage\rdblquote .\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\par
\b\fs24 Game\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\b0\fs20 Resolution modes up to 1920\'d71440 are now supported (dependent on video driver / hardware capability).\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}It is now possible to scroll the viewport all the way to the left and right of a cavern map. Previously, 2 pixels were clipped from each side. This makes bungeeing off the edge of a 3-layer cavern map much easier, because it is now possible to see the bungee cord and worm.\cf1  [What I didn't realise when making this change was, it modifies the game logic; it allows a worm to move 2 pixels farther from the edge without losing its Rope, Bungee, Parachute or Jet Pack.]\cf0\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Fixed \endash  Clicking the mouse wheel or browser button during a game would lock out all keyboard input from then on.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Fixed \endash  Crates sometimes wouldn't fall in a crowded terrain (even at 100% probability). This happened because the game previously used an algorithm that tried up to 75 random positions blindly and then gave up looking; the new algorithm scans every pixel of the map.\cf1  [There is just a tiny flaw in the new algorithm; a crate's collision mask has single-pixel bevels in its corners, but the new algorithm assumes the mask to be rectangular. Known at the time of design, this was deemed acceptable.]\cf0\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Fixed \endash  Graves hit from below could absorb Longbow shots.\cf1  [This was not a complete fix; see v3.6.19.12 for the complete fix.]\cf0\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Fixed \endash  Thinning of some terrain types, occasionally creating openings in solid ground \cf1 [Note: This created blockages in some Battle Race maps designed before the release of this Beta.]\cf0\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Fixed \endash  Parachuting Worm could be hit by a falling worm causing loss of parachute and control. Now your Worm still loses the parachute, but control is retained. \cf1 [Note: This fix inadvertently stopped enemy worms from knocking the attacking worm. This was later fixed in v3.6.19.14.]\cf0\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Fixed \endash  Bungee could fail to activate when walking off a cliff with a crate located directly below, possibly incurring fall damage and loss of turn.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Worms can now change direction and jump in the same instant. When time is critical, and your Worm is limited to ground movement only, it is beneficial to initiate each jump as soon as your Worm has landed and is ready to move. However, upon landing and turning to jump in the opposite direction, it was previously possible to have your direction-change ignored, in the worst-case scenario causing you to jump to death instead of safety.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Cow-doubling glitch is currently disabled. In the future this may be turned into an option.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Crates now automatically fall down at full speed in offline games, instead of parachuting until the player presses Space. Previously, this was the case online but not offline.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The kind of Sheep that jumps out of an exploding crate is now based on the power setting of the Sheep in the current scheme, whereas previously it was hard-coded to a power setting resembling (but not matching) a Sheep set to 3 stars of power.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Select Worm is now disabled for teams that have been reduced to 1 Worm.\par
