\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\b0 The Import function is much faster now (ironically, the pie-shaped progress indicator was hogging lots of CPU time)\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The Import wraparound bug will no longer happen in the majority of cases. The only case in which it may still happen is when importing a 24-bit colour BMP or TGA. (This is a bug that happened when a picture with fewer than 64 non-black colours was Imported.)\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The displayed water level now closely matches what it will look like in-game.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Terrain settings (object / bridge count, border, water level, terrain type) are now retained.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Custom terrains no longer get their object count reset to a very low number.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Removed duplicate reference of "Tribal" terrain.\par
