\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180\b0\fs20 Much improved quick-messaging of people in the lobby, host/join and in-game chats.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Current message typed is retained, while the recipient of the message can be changed. In host/join, the right mouse button now achieves this.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}An \b /ignore\b0  command function is now available for the WormNET lobby which will highlight a name in red and is useful to combat spammers. Typing \b /ignore\b0  alone will clear all ignores.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}W:A now recognises and prints standard IRC CTCP ACTIONs. \cf1 [This was buggy, however; the nickname was omitted, and there was no punctuation to indicate that it was an action. This was later fixed in v3.6.28.0.]\cf0\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}It is now possible to scroll through message chat lists via a mouse wheel; the list must be initially clicked upon and the scrolling is set at one line per wheel bump.\par
