\b\fs24 Fixes\b0\fs20\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li180 W:A no longer uses 100% CPU unnecessarily.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}If you experienced a buggy/laggy timer or inoperational game starting with 3.6.19.17, execute the registry script \b TimerWorkaround_On.reg\b0 . (Note: This setting has no effect under Windows 9x/ME.)\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Bug in a feature introduced in v3.6.19.17: The game no longer freezes when Single Stepping is used up to the end of an Instant Replay.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The Super/Aqua Sheep visual angle now more accurately depicts the angle at which the sheep is flying.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The crosshair visual angle is now more precisely depicted.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The phone icon no longer displays as a result of a whisper which would otherwise be invisible. Note that people with older versions will still see the icon.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}It is no longer possible for a host to start the game on your end if you have not lighted \i on your end\i0  to signal readiness. If the host attempts this, your Ready light bulb will flash; click it to go ahead and start.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Bug introduced in v3.5 Beta 1: With Large Fonts (fonts set to something other than 96 dpi), certain border boxes were drawn with overextended lines.\par
