{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Fixes affecting game logic\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li540 The v3.6.19.17 fix: \i "Weapons can now be selected while your worm is reshooting the Ninja Rope."\i0  introduced a glitch: if you made your worm shoot a starter rope from mid-air, and attempted to select a weapon before the rope caught, the default would be selected instead. It was not intended that selection be possible during the starter rope shot. In v3.6.19.18 the fix for this wasn't complete.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Crates no longer fall slowly following a turn in which Low Gravity was active.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The v3.6.19.7 fix: "\i There was a mismatch between the Fall Damage threshold speed, and the threshold speed at which the Parachute was activated. There was a small space between where your Worm could accrue fall damage without the parachute activating. This only happened when the worm was sliding, for example from the Rope."\i0  was incomplete; there was still a small window between the thresholds. This is now fixed once and for all.\cf1  [Not quite a complete fix; see v3.6.21.1 fixes.]\cf0\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}If a moving worm knocked a mine directly, it was then possible for the worm to pass out of range without triggering the mine.\par
{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}The W:A message format internally allowed a Super/Aqua Sheep to be turned at sudden angles, even full reverse. This would have required hacking, though: it wasn't possible using the keyboard.\par
