\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-270\li270\tx270\b\fs20 1.\b0\tab If a Worm dismounts a horizontally-stationary Ninja Rope in direct contact with the ground, it will land instantly, thus ready to do other things without delay. It is not always possible to extend a rope to the length necessary for this to happen \emdash  since it extends and retracts 4 pixels at a time, it may stop with 1-3 pixels of room remaining between Worm and ground. Also, even if a rope appears to be horizontally stationary, it may have a microscopic amount of momentum. Following are ways to recreate the circumstances required for an instant rope dismount:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li450\i (All versions of W:A)\i0  Worm is standing in a confined space (e.g. at the bottom of a tunnel 9 pixels wide and at least 8 pixels high), and shoots the Ninja Rope straight upward. It may then retract and extend the rope and/or fire a weapon, as long as it does not nudge the rope left or right. Then, when that rope is extended to maximum length (either by not moving at all, or by re-extending the rope as far as it will go) the Worm is in direct contact with the ground.\par
\i{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}(v3.6.23.0 and later)\i0  Same as above, but Worm is not required to fire the rope from a confined space. It may do so from any standing position.\par
\i{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}(v3.6.23.0 and later)\i0  Worm is in midair, with no horizontal velocity, and shoots the Ninja Rope straight upward. There is a 25% chance that the rope will be phased such that it is possible to put the Worm in direct contact with the ground.\par
\i{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}(All versions of W:A)\i0  Same as above, but Worm must be in a 9-pixel-wide tunnel at the time the rope connects.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-270\li270\tx270\b 2.\b0\tab This bug is emulated for compatibility with older versions of W:A. An emulated crash ends the game in a draw for those using a newer version. The older versions will still crash.\par
\b 3.\b0\tab The \b wa://\b0  protocol can be used to join or host games with advanced parameters. The format is \b wa://\b0\i address\b\i0 ?\b0\i param1\b\i0 =\b0\i value1\b\i0 &\b0 ...\b &\b0\i paramN\b\i0 =\b0\i valueN\i0 . Specifying a blank address will cause the game to host a game with the specified parameters. The following parameters are supported:\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li450\b pass\b0  or \b password\b0  \endash  specifies the game's password.\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}id\b0  or \b gameid\b0  \endash  specifies the game's ID, as used on WormNET. \par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}scheme\b0  \endash  specifies the channel scheme to be used. This setting should be identical on all ends. Since this information isn't transmitted via the game peer-to-peer connection, unmatching values can cause a desynchronisation. For more information on the channel scheme format, see \cf4\ul http://worms2d.info/WormNET_(Worms_Armageddon)#Channels\cf0\ulnone\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\li450 Using the scheme parameter, it's possible to create direct IP games with rope knocking enabled. To do this, the host must run \b WA.exe wa://?scheme=Pf\b0  , and other players must run \b WA.exe wa://\b0\i address\b\i0 ?scheme=Pf \b0 .\par
If the game is hosted on a TCP port other than the default one (17011), the port can be specified with the syntax: \b wa://\b0\i address\b\i0 :\b0\i port\b\i0 ?\b0\i parameters\b\i0 ...\b0\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-270\li270\tx270\b 4.\tab\b0 The following registry tweaks allow setting certain game options, most of which can also be set using the \b Advanced Options\b0  screen. These files are located in the \b Tweaks \b0 folder, and are activated by double-clicking them (the game should not be running).\b\fs24\par
\pard{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf8\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\nowidctlpar\fi-180\li450\fs20 BackgroundGradientParallax_Disable.reg\b0 , \b BackgroundGradientParallax_Enable.reg\b0  - enable or disable the dithered gradient parallax effect introduced in the same version. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}FrontendUseDesktopWindow_Enable.reg\b0 , \b FrontendUseDesktopWindow_Disable.reg\b0  - Enables a workaround to allow the front end to render correctly under Wine. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}ForceWineVirtualDesktop_On.reg\b0 , \b ForceWineVirtualDesktop_Off.reg\b0  - Causes W:A to automatically restart itself under a Wine virtual desktop. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}LargerFonts_On.reg\b0 , \b LargerFonts_Off.reg\b0  - Use a larger font in some places in-game and in the front end. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}LegacyUtilityKey_On.reg\b0 , \b LegacyUtilityKey_Off.reg \b0 - Use the key used for typing the \b `\b0  character for the current input language to select utilities, instead of using the key under \b Escape\b0  (for non-US keyboard layouts). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}LoadWormKitModules_Enabled.reg\b0 , \b LoadWormKitModules_Disabled.reg\b0  - Load WormKit modules (DLL files starting with "wk") on startup. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.7.0.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}MapAreaWarnLimit_Always.reg\b0 , \b MapAreaWarnLimit_Default.reg\b0 , \b MapAreaWarnLimit_Unlimited.reg\b0  - Sets the threshold for which to display the map loading prompt, to prevent a Denial of Service attack by loading a very large map. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}SkipIntro_On.reg\b0 , \b SkipIntro_Off.reg\b0  - Skips the intro and logos shown upon W:A startup; identical to the /nointro command line option. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}OfflineRopeKnocking_On.reg\b0 , \b OfflineRopeKnocking_Off.reg\b0  - Enables "rope knocking" in Offline Multi-Player and Quick CPU games. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.24.2)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}Phone_Disable.reg\b0 , \b Phone_Enable.reg\b0  - Disables or enables the in-game telephone icon (used for notification of new chat messages). \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.26.4)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}RegisterAssociations_Automatically.reg\b0 , \b RegisterAssociations_Manually.reg\b0  - Enables associating W:A with replays and wa:// on W:A start-up. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}SlowFrontendWorkaround_Alternative.reg\b0 , \b SlowFrontendWorkaround_Off.reg\b0  - Enables a compatibility tweak for certain new video cards, which may resolve low responsiveness and refresh rates in the front end. Even if there is no frame rate problem, it can reduce the black-out period when switching between front end screens. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.26.5, v3.6.28.0)\cf0\fs20\par
\b{\pntext\f8\'B7\tab}SmoothBackgroundGradient_Disable.reg\b0 , \b SmoothBackgroundGradient_Enable.reg\b0  - Disables or re-enables the dithered background gradient in all in-game detail levels. \cf7\fs14 (introduced in v3.6.30.0)\cf0\fs20\par
